Package portsim.cargo

Class Cargo

  • Object
    • Cargo
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Encodable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    BulkCargo, Container
    public abstract class Cargo
extends Object
implements Encodable
    Denotes a cargo whose function is to be transported via a Ship or land transport.

    Cargo is kept track of via its ID.

    Partially implemented in assignment 1, to be completed in assignment 2

      • toString

        public String toString()
        Returns the human-readable string representation of this cargo.

        The format of the string to return is 

        CargoClass id to destination
        Where:
        • CargoClass is the cargo class name
        • id is the id of this cargo
        • destination is the destination of the cargo

        For example: 

        Container 55 to New Zealand

      • encode

        public String encode()
        Returns the machine-readable string representation of this Cargo.

        The format of the string to return is 

        CargoClass:id:destination
        Where:
        • CargoClass is the Cargo class name
        • id is the id of this cargo
        • destination is the destination of this cargo

        For example: 

        Container:3:Australia
        OR 
        BulkCargo:2:France
        Specified by:
        encode in interface Encodable
        Returns:
        encoded string representation of this Cargo
        Implement this for assignment 2

      • fromString

        public static Cargo fromString​(String string)
                        throws BadEncodingException
        Reads a piece of cargo from its encoded representation in the given string.

        The format of the given string should match the encoded representation of a Cargo, as described in encode() (and subclasses).

        The encoded string is invalid if any of the following conditions are true:

        • The number of colons (:) detected was more/fewer than expected.
        • The cargo id is not an integer (i.e. cannot be parsed by Integer.parseInt(String)).
        • The cargo id is less than one (1).
        • A piece of cargo with the specified ID already exists
        • The cargo type specified is not one of BulkCargoType or ContainerType
        • If the cargo type is a BulkCargo:
          1. The cargo weight in tonnes is not an integer (i.e. cannot be parsed by Integer.parseInt(String)).
          2. The cargo weight in tonnes is less than one (1).
        Parameters:
        string - string containing the encoded cargo
        Returns:
        decoded cargo instance
        Throws:
        BadEncodingException - if the format of the given string is invalid according to the rules above
        Implement this for assignment 2
